---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '@/components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Kontour AI — Transparency building blocks for the AI era"
  description="Kontour AI is building transparency infrastructure that helps humans and agents inspect the evidence behind AI-era claims, decisions, and work."
>
  <Nav active="home" />

  <section class="contour-bg" style="
    position: relative;
    min-height: 100dvh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 8rem var(--spacing-page) 6rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  ">
    <div style="
      position: absolute;
      top: 14%;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translateX(-50%);
      width: 900px;
      height: 620px;
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, rgba(201,163,90,0.045) 0%, transparent 70%);
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 0;
    "></div>

    <div style="max-width: 1180px; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%; position: relative; z-index: 1;">
      <div class="animate-fade-up" style="margin-bottom: 2.25rem;">
        <span class="label-sm">Kontour AI</span>
        <span style="margin: 0 0.75rem; color: var(--color-edge-2);">—</span>
        <span class="label-sm" style="color: var(--color-gold);">Building in progress</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="display-xl animate-fade-up delay-100" style="
        max-width: 980px;
        color: var(--color-chalk);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      ">
        Transparency<br />
        building blocks<br />
        for the AI era.
      </h1>

      <p class="animate-fade-up delay-200" style="
        font-family: var(--font-sans);
        font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.8vw, 1.2rem);
        color: var(--color-chalk-2);
        max-width: 620px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        font-weight: 400;
      ">
        AI systems can now summarize, recommend, approve, ship, and act faster
        than humans can manually inspect. Kontour is building the infrastructure
        that shows the evidence, process state, and readiness signals behind
        what people and agents are asked to trust.
      </p>

      <div class="animate-fade-up delay-300" style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center;">
        <a href="https://github.com/kontourai" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary" data-umami-event="home-hero-github">Follow the build →</a>
        <a href="mailto:hello@kontour.ai" class="btn-ghost" data-umami-event="home-hero-contact">Get in touch</a>
      </div>

      <div class="animate-fade-in delay-500" style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
        margin-top: 4.5rem;
        padding-top: 2.5rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
      ">
        {[
          {
            label: 'Claims',
            body: 'What was asserted, what supports it, and what gap should stay visible.',
            color: 'var(--color-gold)',
          },
          {
            label: 'Processes',
            body: 'Which path was required, which gate passed, and why work advanced.',
            color: 'var(--color-cobalt-2)',
          },
          {
            label: 'Changes',
            body: 'Whether AI-authored work has enough evidence to move forward.',
            color: 'var(--color-green)',
          },
        ].map(({ label, body, color }) => (
          <div style="
            background: rgba(12, 15, 25, 0.72);
            border: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
            border-radius: 6px;
            padding: 1.25rem;
          ">
            <div style={`
              font-family: var(--font-mono);
              font-size: 0.7rem;
              color: ${color};
              letter-spacing: 0.08em;
              text-transform: uppercase;
              margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
            `}>{label}</div>
            <p style="
              color: var(--color-chalk-3);
              font-size: 0.84rem;
              line-height: 1.65;
              margin: 0;
            ">{body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="
    padding: 5rem var(--spacing-page);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
    background: var(--color-ink-1);
  ">
    <div style="max-width: 980px; margin: 0 auto; text-align: center;">
      <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-gold);">Early signal</div>
      <h2 class="display-md" style="color: var(--color-chalk); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
        Evidence-backed confidence.<br />Not certainty theater.
      </h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-2); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0 auto; max-width: 640px;">
        We are still shaping the product line. The public promise is intentionally
        simple for now: make AI-era work more inspectable before people rely on it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer active="home" />
</Layout>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    section div[style*="grid-template-columns: repeat(3"] {
      display: flex !important;
      flex-direction: column !important;
    }
  }
</style>
